<script type="text/javascript">

 function pageNumberValidation(e, form, hiddenField){
   var isNS = (navigator.appName=="Netscape")?1:0;
   var key;

   if (!isNS) {
     key = e.keyCode;
   } else {
     key = e.which;
   }

   if(key == 8 || key == 0){
     return true;
   } else if (key > 47 && key < 58) {
      return true; 
   }else if(key == 13) {
      hiddenField.value = "true";
      form.submit();
   }
   return false;
}

</script>

<!--

function checkExportFormat(limit) {

    var msg = "";

    for (i=0;i<document.exportCite.elements.length;i++) {
        if (document.exportCite.elements[i].value == "REFWX") {
            if (document.exportCite.elements[i].checked) {
                document.exportCite.setAttribute('target',"RefWorksMain");
                if (checkLimit()) {
                    if (limit) {
                        msg = "It is possible 
that some users may experience problems when downloading large numbers 
of citations. If this happens please contact RefWorks support at your 
regionally hosted site or e-mail support@refworks.com to assist you 
further.\n\n";
                    }
                    msg += "Exporting to RefWorks may take some time, please wait....";
                    alert(msg);
                }
            }
            else {
                document.exportCite.setAttribute('target',"");
            }
            break;
        }
    }
    return true;
}

function determineCount(numStr) {
    var count=1;

    if(numStr.indexOf("-")) {
        var rangeStr = numStr.split("-");

        if(rangeStr.length == 2) {
            var highNum = parseInt(rangeStr[1]);
            var lowNum = parseInt(rangeStr[0]);

            if(highNum >= lowNum) { count = (highNum - lowNum) + 1; }
        }
    }
    return count;
}

function checkLimit(){

    var selectNum = "";
    var useSelected = false;
    var allNum = 0;
    var count = 0;
    var rdoc = 0;

    for (i=0;i<document.exportCite.elements.length;i++) {
        if (document.exportCite.elements[i].name == "count") {
            allNum = document.exportCite.elements[i].value;
        }
        if (document.exportCite.elements[i].name == "NUMBER_LIST") {
            selectNum = document.exportCite.elements[i].value;
        }
        if (document.exportCite.elements[i].name == "_rdoc") {
            rdoc = document.exportCite.elements[i].value;
        }
        if (document.exportCite.elements[i].value == "selected") {
            if (document.exportCite.elements[i].checked) {
                useSelected = true;
            }
        }
    }

    if (useSelected) {
        selectNum = selectNum.replace(/ /g,"");
        if(selectNum.indexOf(",")) {
            var commaList = selectNum.split(",");
            for(i=0; i < commaList.length; i++) {
                count += determineCount(commaList[i]);
            }
        }
        else {
            count += determineCount(selectNum);
        }
    }
    else { 
        if (rdoc > 0) {
            count = 1;
        }
        else {
            count = allNum;
        }
    }

    if(count > 50) { return true; }
  
    return false;
}

//-->

</ul><div id="abs_S073386191300090X" class="previewBox abstract hidden"></div><div id="rabs_S073386191300090X" class="previewBox rabstract hidden"></div><div id="gabs_S073386191300090X" class="previewBox gabstract hidden"></div></div></li><li class="teaserAbs "><div><?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><div class="svAbstract" data-etype="ab"><div class="articleText"><div class="articleText_indent"><p class="paraText">Imaging
 equipment is experiencing advances in speed, sensitivity, safety, and 
workflow. There is an increasing trend toward physiologic imaging and 
quantitation, requiring greater consistency across manufacturers and 
clinics. The Human Connectome Project is symbolic of the drive toward 
combining multimodality anatomic and functional imaging with 
quantitation and sophisticated atlases. Advanced visualization methods 
have become essential in the evaluation of large multidimensional data 
sets. Hybrid imaging blends advantages from multiple modalities to 
provide a comprehensive anatomic, functional, physiologic, and metabolic
 data set. Breakthrough clinical neuroimaging applications are derived 
from an alignment of scientific, engineering, clinical, and business 
conditions.</div></div></div></div></li><li class="accessBlock colLast"><span class="dsub_article_sci_dir sci_dir" title="Entitled to full text" alt="Entitled to full text">&nbsp;<span class="offscreen">Entitled to full text</span></span></li></ul></li><div id="resultsView_82" class="resultsView"></div><li class="detail"><ul class="article"><li class="selection"><input class="checkBox" type="checkbox" name="art" value="3-s2.0-B978012397010700001X" aria-labelledby="title_B978012397010700001X" style="padding-left:6px;"></li><li class="title "><H2> <a id ="title_B978012397010700001X" href="http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/B978012397010700001X" class="cLink artTitle S_C_artTitle " data-docsubtype="chp" queryStr="?_rdoc=83&_fmt=high&_origin=search&_docanchor=&_ct=233&_zone=rslt_list_item&md5=52ea8600159a60afa6a197c5bc072df3">1 - Introduction</a></H2></li><li class="source "><i>Temporal QOS Management in Scientific Cloud Workflow Systems</i>, <i>2012</i>, <i>Pages 1-10</i></li><li class="authorTxt ">Xiao Liu, Yun Yang, Jinjun Chen</li><li class="external "><div class="txt external"><ul class="extLinkBlock"><li><a href="#" data-type="abstract" role="button" class="absLink" data-url="http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/preview/abstract?_rdoc=83&_origin=search&_ct=233&_zone=rslt_list_item&_fmt=full&_pii=B978012397010700001X&_isbn=9780123970107&_tab=afr&absLinks=y&md5=b93e495db5cffef7faed0a1bef9553d1" aria-describedby="title_B978012397010700001X" aria-controls="abs_B978012397010700001X" aria-expanded="false"><span class="arrowSide"></span><span class="preTxt">Abstract</span></a></li><li><a aria-describedby="title_B978012397010700001X"  rel="nofollow" href="/science?_ob=ShoppingCartURL&_method=add&_eid=3-s2.0-B978012397010700001X&_ts=1447785910&md5=b673f2048afb79cb95f3ca160c53569d"><span class="pdfIconSmall">&nbsp;</span>Purchase PDF</a></li>
